# Personal task files — Gary's own, not for distribution. This repo runs on
# one machine; nothing under tasks/ is shared. ONLY the generic example is
# tracked. Everything else stays local, including anything created later.
# The launchd plists are the one exception (see below).
#
# The personal task files remain runtime dependencies — read by the launchd
# jobs and proactive/sweep.ts — so they must exist on disk here. They are
# simply no longer distributed via git.
tasks/*
!tasks/.gitkeep
!tasks/EXAMPLE-task.md
# The launchd plists are install machinery, not personal content: they carry no
# operator name and no absolute path — scripts/install.sh stamps __REPO_PATH__
# at install time. scripts/install.test.ts reads them from the checkout, so
# untracking them fails 26 tests on any clean clone.
!tasks/*-launchd.plist

# Local agent config and personal artifacts — same principle as tasks/ above:
# this repo runs on one machine, so none of it is distributed. All of it is
# still read locally at runtime; it is simply not tracked.
#
#   .claude/            settings.local.json, test_command (the commit test
#                       gate reads this), eval artifacts, worktrees
#   evals/              behavioural eval specs and their recorded results
#   workflow.config.yaml  carries an absolute wiki_path under /Users/harrison
.claude/
evals/
workflow.config.yaml

# The operator's own system prompt. prompts/system.md (tracked) is generic and
# names nobody; this file overrides it when present and never ships.
# See resolveSystemPromptPath in proactive/systemPrompt.ts for the order.
prompts/system.local.md
